<h2 id="20">2. Booking a plentymarkets POS</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To use plentymarkets POS, you need to book one or more POS in plentymarkets. Visit our plentymarkets POS product page to find further information on prices and conditions.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="30">3. Setting up a POS for a client</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once you have booked a POS, you configure it in the plentymarkets back end. You assign a POS to a client by creating and configuring a POS in the <strong>System » Client » Select client » POS</strong> menu. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="40">3.1. Creating a POS for a client</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, create a POS for the client (store) in the plentymarkets back end.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a POS for a client:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » POS</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New POS</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>New POS</strong> will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the POS.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ A referrer will be assigned to the POS.<br>
→ The POS will be created and the settings will be displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Table 1 describes the menu bar of a POS.</p>
