<h2 id="_preparing_gift_card_sales">10. Preparing gift card sales</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Gift cards are sold by selling coupon items in plentymarkets. When you sell a coupon item, you provide customers with a coupon code. Customers only can redeem a coupon code if their coupon code is saved in the plentymarkets back end at the time the customers tries to redeem it. You either can generate coupon codes automatically or work with your own coupon codes.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following preparations in the plentymarkets back end are necessary to sell gift cards via plentymarkets POS:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Create a coupon campaign of the type <strong>Gift card</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Create a free text field for the campaign and link it in the <strong>System » Orders » Coupons</strong> menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Create gift card items with a VAT rate of 0%.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Link the gift card item to the campaign.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Generate coupon codes or save your own coupon codes in the back end.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Create gift card templates and make them available to POS users.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Make coupon codes available to POS users.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Activate rights</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For POS users with a variable user class, you need to activate the rights <strong>Create code</strong> and <strong>Show code</strong>. These rights are set in the <strong>System » Settings » User » Open user » Tab: Right » Tab: REST-API</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>These steps are described here. Find more detailed information on gift cards and coupons on the <strong><a href="/en/order-processing/orders/coupons">Coupons</a></strong> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">More than one POS</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Do you have more than one POS and create your own coupon codes? Divide the printed coupon codes between the different POS or create a separate coupon campaign and gift card items to make sure that each coupon code is sold only once.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_preparing_the_free_text_field">10.1. Preparing the free text field</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To sell gift cards, you need to link the gift card item to a free text field. You define this free text field and assign it to a coupon campaign. A free text field needs to be defined only once.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="820">10.1.1. Defining the free text field</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Define the free text field to be used for campaigns.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Defining the free text field:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Item » Free text fields</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Field name</strong> field, enter <strong>Kampaign ID</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> Pay attention to the correct spelling. The name <strong>Kampagne ID</strong> is valid only as specified here.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the data type <strong>number</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the character length.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The free text field is activated over night and available the next day.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_selecting_a_free_text_field">10.1.2. Selecting a free text field</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Now, go to <strong>System » Orders » Coupons</strong>. Select this free text field and link it to a coupon campaign. You only need to do this once for all campaigns.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Selecting a free text field:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Orders » Coupons</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the campaign field <strong>Campaign ID</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The <strong>Kampagne ID</strong> field is shown in the <strong><a href="/en/item/managing-items#75">Fields</a></strong> tab of the item.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="830">10.2. Creating a campaign for POS gift cards</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Now, create one or several campaigns for selling gift cards in plentymarkets POS. You have the following options:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>You create one campaign for all gift cards you sell in plentymarkets POS.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You create one campaign per gift card value.<br>
<strong><em>Example:</em></strong> You want to sell gift cards for 10 GBP, 25 GBP and 50 GBP and a gift card with a flexible value that POS users enter during the transaction. As such, you create 3 campaigns with the discount values 10, 25 and 50 GBP and a campaign with an amount of your choice.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you operate more than one POS and want to use your own coupon codes it also may make sense to create separate campaigns for each POS.</p>
</div>
